The '''Heinrich Wieland Prize''' is an annual science award for research on [[lipid]]s in the fields of [[chemistry]], [[biochemistry]], [[physiology]] and [[clinical medicine]]. It is sponsored by [[Boehringer Ingelheim]], and awarded by a board of trustees. The prize is named after the Nobel Prize Laureate in chemistry Professor [[Heinrich Wieland]] (1877-1957), one of the leading lipid chemists of the first half of the 20th century.

